      <scopecontent id="aspace_bdd05f9608d121be914e03d00972e856">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The John Moore Papers consist of sixty-six letters written by John Moore, mostly to his mother and sister, Eveline (Moore) Burleigh in Massachusetts, from 1837 to 1866. Moore, who was born in Massachusetts, moved to Talladega, Alabama. Although he was educated as a doctor, he there entered the mercantile business. By 1855 he had lost all his property and moved to Texas as a result, finally settling in Manchaca. His letters provided a fairly detailed description of the climate, soil, economic potential and the people of the various places in which he lived. Accompanying the correspondence is a microfilm containing typed manuscripts of the letters.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <bioghist id="aspace_2a68a945ef94934f935af811d780baa2">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>John Moore was born in Massachusetts and moved to Talladega, Alabama. Although he was educated as a doctor, he entered the mercantile business in Alabama. He lost all his property in 1855 and moved to Texas.</p>  
      </bioghist>
